# Spectres Runtime — environment configuration TEMPLATE.
#
# This file IS committed to git. NEVER put a real secret here. It documents every
# key, its recommended value, and the rationale. `config.Settings` declares no
# defaults, so these values are the single source of truth.
#
# Usage: copy this file to `.env` (git-ignored) and put your real secrets in THAT
# copy, not here. Every key below maps 1:1 to a field on
# `spectres_runtime.config.Settings` (case-insensitive).

# --- Datastore ---------------------------------------------------------------
# Postgres + pgvector connection URL. Matches docker/compose.yaml (host port 5532,
# Agno's convention to avoid clashing with a standard local Postgres on 5432).
DATABASE_URL=postgresql+psycopg://ai:ai@localhost:5532/ai

# --- Embedding provider (hosted, OpenAI-compatible) --------------------------
# The model name is a DATA CONTRACT: stored vectors are only queryable by the SAME
# model that produced them, so changing this means a full re-embed. Working default
# is SiliconFlow Qwen3-Embedding-0.6B. Provider-agnostic — point EMBEDDER_BASE_URL
# at any OpenAI-compatible endpoint (SiliconFlow, DashScope, ...) to swap vendors.
EMBEDDER_MODEL=Qwen/Qwen3-Embedding-0.6B

# Mainland SiliconFlow host. The `.cn` host is a separate account/key namespace
# from the international `.com` host — use the one your API key belongs to.
EMBEDDER_BASE_URL=https://api.siliconflow.cn/v1

# Embedding vector size. Qwen3-Embedding-0.6B is MRL-configurable (32-1024); 1024
# is its native max and stays <=2000, so the column remains pgvector-indexable
# later if the corpus grows.
EMBEDDER_DIMENSIONS=1024

# SECRET — set this only in your local `.env`, never in this template. Obtain it
# from your SiliconFlow (.cn) account. Required for any live embed call (ingest +
# search).
EMBEDDER_API_KEY=sk-replace-me-in-dotenv
